1
00:00:01,334 --> 00:00:02,711
<i>Alice, what's the matter?</i>

2
00:00:02,794 --> 00:00:03,837
<i>It's Kyle.</i>

3
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:05,255
<i>He was here in Amurao.</i>

4
00:00:05,338 --> 00:00:07,048
<i>- Kyle Sebastian?</i>
<i>- Yes.</i>

5
00:00:07,132 --> 00:00:10,051
<i>He had a good reason</i>
<i>to kill Louisa, remember?</i>

6
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,264
<i>- Are you all right?</i>
<i>- Thank you.</i>

7
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:17,559
<i>If you're free later,</i>
<i>we hang out at the boardwalk, come by.</i>

8
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:18,935
<i>Why are we here?</i>

9
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:20,895
<i>This is where I go</i>
<i>whenever I have a problem.</i>

10
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:22,063
<i>What are you doing?!</i>

11
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:24,441
<i>- Get off me!</i>
- [thuds]

12
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:28,737
<i>There's now a new whore in Amurao!</i>

13
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:30,530
[students laughing]

14
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:31,364
<i>Rapist.</i>

15
00:00:31,448 --> 00:00:32,365
<i>What did you say?</i>

16
00:00:32,449 --> 00:00:34,117
<i>Rapist!</i> [groans]

17
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,660
<i>Let her go!</i>

18
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,871
[groaning]

19
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:41,624
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
dark instrumental playing]

20
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:44,210
<i>- Papa!</i>
- [groans]

21
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:47,213
[crashing, shattering]

22
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:55,263
[theme music playing]

23
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:06,126
- <i>Let me go!</i>
- [yelps]

24
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:10,088
- [thuds]
- [young Kyle groans]

25
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:12,507
- [Beth inhales sharply]
- [young Kyle groans]

26
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:16,594
- [high-pitched tone]
- [heart beating steadily]

27
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:22,392
- [tone fades]
- [heart beat continues]

28
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:28,523
[principal] Miss Soria!

29
00:02:31,317 --> 00:02:34,279
<i>Mr. Sebastian said you hurt him first.</i>

30
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:36,573
<i>I just confronted him!</i>

31
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:37,699
[principal] <i>About what?</i>

32
00:02:43,288 --> 00:02:45,790
<i>He's spreading lies about me.</i>

33
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:47,167
[principal] <i>Whatever the reason is,</i>

34
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,586
<i>we don't condone violence in this school!</i>

35
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:51,045
<i>Ma'am, I didn't hurt him.</i>

36
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:53,756
<i>Then why is Mr. Sebastian in the hospital?</i>

37
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:56,259
<i>Then ask them who started it!</i>

38
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:57,969
<i>They saw it all!</i>

39
00:02:58,052 --> 00:03:02,849
[tense music plays]

40
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:06,352
<i>Um…</i>

41
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:12,066
<i>It was Louisa who started the argument.</i>

42
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:16,279
<i>But, it was Kyle who hit her first.</i>

43
00:03:17,071 --> 00:03:20,074
<i>I didn't see the fight from</i>
<i>the beginning, but Mel's right.</i>

44
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:21,451
<i>I saw the same thing.</i>

45
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:22,911
<i>Me too!</i>

46
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:26,164
<i>Mr. Sebastian said you'd say that.</i>

47
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,708
<i>But he said you all ganged up on him.</i>

48
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:29,709
<i>Excuse me?</i>

49
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:31,002
<i>What?!</i>

50
00:03:31,085 --> 00:03:32,670
[principal] <i>This is a serious matter.</i>

51
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:35,256
<i>I'll call your parents here tomorrow.</i>

52
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:38,384
<i>But, ma'am,</i>
<i>we really didn't do anything to him!</i>

53
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,720
<i>She's the only one who pushed him, not us!</i>

54
00:03:40,803 --> 00:03:43,431
<i>Ma'am, they're not</i>
<i>involved in my argument with Kyle.</i>

55
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:45,558
<i>Please don't drag them into this.</i>

56
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:48,353
[tense music continues, fades]

57
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:49,771
<i>Erica!</i>

58
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:54,943
<i>Thank you for helping earlier.</i>

59
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:01,532
<i>You know, you're quiet, but…</i>

60
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:03,868
<i>you're quite tough yourself.</i> [chuckles]

61
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:07,580
<i>But…</i>

62
00:04:08,831 --> 00:04:10,083
<i>I'm sorry, Erica.</i>

63
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:14,837
<i>I'm sure your parents will</i>
<i>get mad at you because of me.</i>

64
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:18,132
[Erica clicks tongue, inhales deeply]

65
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:19,717
<i>I don't have a father.</i>

66
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,888
<i>My mother doesn't care about me either.</i>

67
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:27,267
<i>Hey, Louisa!</i>

68
00:04:28,851 --> 00:04:31,688
<i>If what you're saying about Kyle is true,</i>

69
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:34,691
<i>then why didn't you say</i>
<i>that to the principal earlier?</i>

70
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:41,614
[sighs] <i>You know my brother, don't you?</i>

71
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:47,412
<i>If I told her,</i>
<i>my brother would know and he'd go mad.</i>

72
00:04:47,829 --> 00:04:49,247
<i>He might even beat up Kyle.</i>

73
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,165
<i>He might kill someone.</i>

74
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:54,502
<i>I don't want that to happen.</i>

75
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:58,381
<i>But now, it's us who got involved!</i>

76
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,634
<i>- If I get suspended because of you--</i>
<i>- No, I'll fix it tomorrow.</i>

77
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:02,885
<i>I'll talk to the principal.</i>

78
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:04,262
<i>So you should!</i>

79
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,264
<i>My record's perfect, okay?</i>

80
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:10,184
<i>I won't let it get ruined</i>
<i>just because Kyle deceived you.</i>

81
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,479
[exhales heavily]

82
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:21,654
<i>Wait a second.</i>

83
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:25,283
<i>She said that Kyle deceived me, right?</i>

84
00:05:26,951 --> 00:05:29,037
<i>Does that mean she believes me?</i>

85
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,874
<i>You are telling the truth.</i>

86
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:35,251
<i>I know that.</i>

87
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:40,089
[tender music plays]

88
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:42,133
<i>Are you all right?</i>

89
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:46,929
<i>No one has even asked you how you're doing</i>
<i>after what Kyle did to you.</i>

90
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:50,391
[uneasy music playing]

91
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,602
<i>- Let's stay here first, Louisa.</i>
- [Louisa yelps]

92
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:53,561
<i>Come on</i>

93
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,229
<i>- Let me go, Kyle!</i>
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

94
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:56,731
<i>Stop complaining!</i>

95
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:58,441
[uneasy music fades]

96
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:00,902
<i>I'll be okay.</i>

97
00:06:00,985 --> 00:06:05,073
[unsettling music playing]

98
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,242
[exhales sharply]

99
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:15,625
But then, my dad died, so…

100
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:19,253
I wasn't there when
the principal talked with your parents.

101
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:23,674
[unsettling music continues]

102
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:26,677
[music fades]

103
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:27,845
[principal] <i>As you can see,</i>

104
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:30,723
<i>I didn't ask Alice Quintana</i>
<i>and her mother to attend anymore.</i>

105
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:34,310
<i>Erica's mother also can't</i>
<i>be with us today.</i>

106
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,354
<i>I apologize.</i>

107
00:06:37,313 --> 00:06:38,815
<i>You all know why we're here.</i>

108
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,734
<i>The good news is that I've agreed</i>

109
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:44,529
<i>with Kyle and Mr. and Mrs. Sebastian</i>

110
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:48,491
<i>not suspend Erica, Mel, Beth, and Louisa.</i>

111
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:52,829
<i>All they want is for</i>
<i>the girls to understand…</i>

112
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,413
<i>the severity of their actions…</i>

113
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,583
<i>and they want</i>
<i>the girls to apologize to Kyle.</i>

114
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:02,505
[uneasy music plays, fades]

115
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:06,884
[Kyle's mother] <i>I just</i>
<i>want to remind you that…</i>

116
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:10,388
<i>if a man rejects you,</i>

117
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:11,889
<i>learn to accept it.</i>

118
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:15,560
<i>You shouldn't hurt or coerce anyone.</i>

119
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:18,187
<i>Tell that to your son.</i>

120
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:19,897
<i>Excuse me?</i>

121
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:22,525
[Marie] <i>Uh, ma'am…</i>

122
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:25,820
<i>Based on what my daughter told me,</i>

123
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:27,822
<i>she didn't do anything wrong.</i>

124
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:30,575
<i>My son fell down the stairs!</i>

125
00:07:30,658 --> 00:07:32,535
<i>And they didn't do anything wrong?</i>

126
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:34,454
<i>Don't try to argue in English with me!</i>

127
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:37,540
<i>I believe what my child told me!</i>

128
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:40,251
<i>That's right.</i>

129
00:07:40,334 --> 00:07:42,253
<i>Beth is a good kid.</i>

130
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:43,671
<i>That's enough!</i>

131
00:07:45,173 --> 00:07:47,175
<i>- Mrs. Sevilla--</i>
<i>- Miss!</i>

132
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,345
<i>It seems you didn't</i>
<i>raise your child properly.</i>

133
00:07:51,846 --> 00:07:54,015
<i>Now, I teach my daughter accountability,</i>

134
00:07:54,765 --> 00:07:57,435
<i>to take responsibility for her mistakes.</i>

135
00:07:58,144 --> 00:07:59,812
<i>I know the Sebastians.</i>

136
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,189
<i>I also know Kyle well.</i>

137
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,567
<i>He is a good and upstanding young man.</i>

138
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:07,778
<i>So if there's someone lying here…</i>

139
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:10,948
<i>it's not him.</i>

140
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:12,241
- [thuds]
<i>- Hey!</i>

141
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:13,868
<i>You've been ganging up on my sister!</i>

142
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:15,995
<i>You're siding with them</i>
<i>just because they're rich?</i>

143
00:08:16,078 --> 00:08:16,871
<i>Brother!</i>

144
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:21,250
<i>I regret not teaching my</i>
<i>child how to choose her friends.</i>

145
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,586
<i>Now, that's me taking</i>
<i>accountability as a parent.</i>

146
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:25,046
[scoffs] <i>Accountability?</i>

147
00:08:25,129 --> 00:08:26,672
<i>And now, it's my daughter's turn.</i>

148
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,424
And she knows that.

149
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:30,760
<i>Try to be good parents, too.</i>

150
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:32,762
<i>Oh, ma'am!</i>

151
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:36,599
<i>I wasn't informed</i>
<i>that I joined a seminar today…</i>

152
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:41,270
<i>on how to be a good parent!</i>

153
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:42,980
[principal] <i>Um, Mrs. Sevilla…</i>

154
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:46,025
<i>I'm sure that's not what Dr.</i>
<i>Barrera intended.</i>

155
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:48,110
<i>Ma'am, did you even investigate?</i>

156
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,655
<i>Why are you just believing what they said?</i>

157
00:08:50,738 --> 00:08:52,240
[Cedric] <i>This is ridiculous!</i>

158
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,241
[Lemuel scoffs] <i>Ridiculous?</i>

159
00:08:53,324 --> 00:08:55,368
[Cedric] <i>I took time off</i>
<i>from the hospital for what?</i>

160
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:56,452
<i>For this?!</i>

161
00:08:57,245 --> 00:08:58,496
<i>I'll apologize.</i>

162
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,123
[Lemuel] <i>Why are you saying sorry?</i>

163
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:02,959
<i>That's what Kyle wants anyway, right?</i>

164
00:09:03,042 --> 00:09:04,252
<i>Then I'll do it.</i>

165
00:09:05,461 --> 00:09:08,089
<i>But Mel, Beth, and Erica</i>
<i>shouldn't need to do the same…</i>

166
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:10,925
<i>because they've done nothing wrong.</i>

167
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:15,179
[morose music playing]

168
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:16,681
<i>- Louisa…</i>
<i>- Sister!</i>

169
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:24,313
<i>I'm sorry for what happened to your son.</i>

170
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:28,109
<i>It wasn't my plan for</i>
<i>him to fall down the stairs.</i>

171
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:32,280
[morose music continues]

172
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:40,538
<i>Sorry.</i>

173
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,833
[Lemuel] <i>Louisa!</i>

174
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:44,917
<i>Louisa!</i>

175
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:48,462
[music fades]

176
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:49,505
[young Alice] <i>Ma?</i>

177
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,340
<i>I'm now with them.</i>

178
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:53,801
<i>Perhaps in an hour?</i>

179
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,178
<i>Okay, Ma.</i>

180
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,183
<i>Are you okay?</i>

181
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:05,646
<i>What?</i>

182
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,359
<i>You sounded too kind.</i>

183
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:12,236
<i>It doesn't suit you.</i>

184
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,572
- [playful music playing]
<i>- So, what do you want to say?</i>

185
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:16,407
<i>That I'm not usually kind?</i>

186
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:18,409
<i>Well, yes.</i>

187
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:20,661
[chuckling]

188
00:10:20,745 --> 00:10:22,580
<i>You can't argue with me.</i>

189
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,957
<i>I didn't say anything.</i>

190
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,250
<i>If I'm not kind,</i>

191
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:29,211
<i>would I still go to a burning car for you?</i>

192
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,799
<i>- Sorry.</i>
<i>- It's fine.</i>

193
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:40,473
<i>Actually, I haven't thanked you yet.</i>

194
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:42,767
[tender music playing]

195
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,018
<i>Thank you.</i>

196
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:50,232
<i>Mama said some adults</i>
<i>were even too afraid to help.</i>

197
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:51,942
<i>But you guys…</i>

198
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:55,363
<i>You risked your lives for me.</i>

199
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:57,573
<i>But why did you do that?</i>

200
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,076
[young Beth] <i>Maybe…</i>

201
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,995
<i>It's because we knew</i>
<i>you were inside the car.</i>

202
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:04,955
[young Mel] <i>It just happened.</i>

203
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,666
<i>Look at these two.</i>

204
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:09,627
<i>They went in even</i>
<i>when the fire was got worse.</i>

205
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:11,462
<i>I only followed her lead.</i>

206
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:15,758
[tender music continues]

207
00:11:15,841 --> 00:11:17,301
<i>I'm the reason why…</i>

208
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:19,678
<i>you were going there in the first place.</i>

209
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:23,224
<i>If it weren't for Kyle…</i>

210
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:27,311
<i>your dad wouldn't drive</i>
<i>you to buy you a milkshake.</i>

211
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:28,854
<i>Right?</i>

212
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:33,442
<i>Louisa, it's not your fault.</i>

213
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:35,861
<i>Even if Kyle's situation hadn't happen,</i>

214
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,988
<i>we'd still get in an accident because</i>

215
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:39,782
<i>the brakes of the truck were broken.</i>

216
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:43,244
<i>If you also blame yourself</i>
<i>for the accident because of him,</i>

217
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:46,747
<i>you're just handing</i>
<i>Kyle another point over us.</i>

218
00:11:46,831 --> 00:11:48,207
<i>Another point?</i>

219
00:11:48,749 --> 00:11:50,918
<i>The principal made Louisa apologize</i>

220
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,503
<i>to him and his parents.</i>

221
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,423
<i>Oh my goodness!</i>

222
00:11:56,924 --> 00:11:58,008
<i>Are you okay?</i>

223
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:00,052
[sighs]

224
00:12:00,719 --> 00:12:03,764
<i>That was just</i>
<i>an apology. I'll get over it.</i>

225
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:07,435
[tender music continues, fades]

226
